---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Tony Long II — ExpatBuildr"
  description="American founder building from Cebu, Philippines. The story behind ExpatBuildr — losing $300K in crypto, moving abroad, and building in public."
  canonicalUrl="https://expatbuildr.com/about"
  ogImage="/expatog.jpg"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 px-6">

    <header class="mb-16 reveal-on-scroll">
      <p class="text-[10px] font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.4em] text-accent-blue mb-4">
        Founder / Origin Story
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-8xl font-black font-display tracking-tighter leading-none mb-6 text-slate-900 dark:text-white uppercase">
        ABOUT<br/>
        <span class="text-slate-900/20 dark:text-white/20">ME.</span>
      </h1>
    </header>

    <section class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-start mb-16 reveal-on-scroll">
      <div class="shrink-0 mx-auto md:mx-0">
        <div class="glass-card rounded-3xl p-2 w-48 md:w-56">
          <img
            src="/authors/galaxy.jpg"
            alt="Tony Long II"
            class="rounded-2xl w-full aspect-square object-cover"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1 text-center md:text-left">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black font-display tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
          Tony Long II
        </h2>
        <p class="text-accent-blue font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">
          Founder, ExpatBuildr · Cebu, Philippines
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          I lost $300K in crypto. Not in one trade — in a series of increasingly confident bets on things I couldn't control. <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white">Skill in a bad position still loses.</strong>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="prose">
      <section class="space-y-4">
        <p>
          That loss forced me to look at everything differently. Not just how I earn money — but where I earn it, where I spend it, and what systems I build in between.
        </p>
        <p>
          I moved to Cebu, Philippines. Started earning in USD. Spending in pesos. The gap between those two currencies became my weapon. <strong>That's arbitrage.</strong> It works in 15 countries. I'm running it from one of them — and building it all in public.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today I run Galaxy Arbitrage Weekly, a newsletter for Americans living abroad, and ExpatBuildr, a studio building landing pages and conversion funnels for expat founders. ExpatBuildr is where I document all of it — the wins, the math, and the mistakes.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-slate-900/10 dark:border-white/10 text-center">
      <a href="/newsletter" class="btn-primary">Join the newsletter →</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
